SEMDL Help Topic: reference normalize

Usage:
- `ssd normalize <input.ssd> [--stdout]`

Status:
- `--stdout` returns canonical inline output from `.ssd` with an optional paired `.ssm`.
- Bare `ssd normalize <input.ssd>` currently applies only to standalone `.ssd` inputs without a paired `.ssm`.

Related help:
- `ssd help grammar`
- `ssd help troubleshooting`
